parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: LP Line Rupture due to Proximity to Left Rear Inner Tire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rupture of the LP line can cause a significant release of propane gas, which can lead to a fire hazard, explosion, or asphyxiation, potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: hissing sound from the LP line

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank venting system can cause fuel to discharge from the vent with force, resulting in environmental pollution and a high risk of ignition, which can lead to catastrophic consequences, including destruction of the vehicle, injury, or loss of life.
symptoms: Pulsing noise in the fuel tank when refueling
fuel discharging from the fuel tank vent with force
discharge continues as long as the pulsing noise continues
discharged amount measures from 1/2 pint to 1&1/2 gallons.
